Hi Team,

Key Discussion Points
1. Wiki Audience & Purpose
Wiki should act as a single source of truth primarily for Developers and QA teams.
Each wiki page should include a brief introduction/overview explaining:
What the topic is.
Its purpose.
Topics covered in the page.
A short summary at the top will help users quickly understand page content.
2. Introduction & Access Information
Login/access details can be retained if required.
Avoid referencing specific individuals for access requests.
Use generic references instead of personal names.
Links that may change over time should either be:
Referred to generically, or
Marked as TBD until finalized.
3. Reusable Content Strategy
Common sections such as:
Block Scenarios
Address/Contact Management
Product Validations
API related wiki pages
Should be maintained as separate reusable wiki pages and referenced through links from intake-specific pages.
This approach improves maintainability and reduces duplication.
4. Documentation Standards
Need uniformity across all wiki pages:
Consistent font type.
Consistent heading hierarchy.
Consistent font sizes.
Consistent colors.
Consistent alignment and formatting.
Spell-check before publishing.
Uniform terminology and naming conventions across all pages.
Avoid mixing hyphens, spaces, capitalization, quotes, and formatting styles within the same documentation set.
6. Content Quality Expectations
Wiki should not be a direct copy of user manuals.
Team should:
Review and understand existing documentation.
Add business rules and functional logic.
Capture tribal knowledge and hidden dependencies.
Include troubleshooting and operational knowledge wherever applicable
7. Technical Content Inclusion
Approved additions:
SOQL queries.
Object API names.
Field API names.
Custom setting details.
Integration/API references via linked pages.
Functional and technical dependencies
8. Security Considerations
Do not document:
Passwords.
Keys.
Secrets.
Confidential credentials.
Any sensitive integration authentication details.
